# Bundled .deb directory.
#
# This folder ships a verified yad .deb (and any of its missing dependencies)
# so the BoT control panel can be installed on a fresh Tails session without
# requiring "Additional Software" persistence to be enabled first.
#
# The bundle is regenerated before each release by running
# `tools/fetch-yad-deb.sh` on a Tails laptop. The expected layout is:
#
#     debs/
#       yad_<version>_amd64.deb
#       SHA256SUMS              # one line per .deb in this folder
#
# Both `persistent-setup` and `bot-menu` will look here on first run, verify
# SHA256SUMS, and install via `apt-get install ./yad_*.deb` so dependency
# resolution still happens through apt.
